        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Reverse Entry for Migrant Offenders and Violence Expulsion Act</b></p> <p>This bill establishes under statute that a conviction for certain crimes related to kidnapping or sexual abuse shall be grounds for (1) barring an individual from entering the United States, and (2) deportability. (Under current law, convictions for certain crimes, including crimes involving moral turpitude, are grounds for inadmissibility and deportability.)<br> </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
